# Soundness regression: a def's declared generic must hold for EVERY
# instantiation, not just the one an overload arm happens to pick.
#
# The quote `(@x toFloat)` only produces Maybe[float] when `a` is str;
# for `a` = int it produces a bare float. Accepting this def lets the
# caller below pass an int, and `?` then crashes at runtime on the
# non-Maybe value. The checker must reject the def: `toFloat` cannot
# accept a rigid generic `a`.
def pick2 (a -- Maybe[float])
  x!
  true (@x toFloat) (none) iff
end
3 pick2 ? str wl
